### Update Booking Details This API endpoint is used to update the details of a booking by making an HTTP PUT request to `https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking/4099`. #### Request Body - The request should include a JSON payload with the following parameters: - `firstname` (string): The first name of the guest. - `lastname` (string): The last name of the guest. - `totalprice` (number): The total price of the booking. - `depositpaid` (boolean): Indicates if the deposit has been paid. - `bookingdates` (object): An object containing the check-in and check-out dates. - `checkin` (string): The check-in date in the format "YYYY-MM-DD". - `checkout` (string): The check-out date in the format "YYYY-MM-DD". - `additionalneeds` (string): Any additional needs or requests for the booking. #### Response (200 - OK) The response will be in JSON format with the following schema: ``` json { "type": "object", "properties": { "firstname": { "type": "string" }, "lastname": { "type": "string" }, "totalprice": { "type": "number" }, "depositpaid": { "type": "boolean" }, "bookingdates": { "type": "object", "properties": { "checkin": { "type": "string" }, "checkout": { "type": "string" } } }, "additionalneeds": { "type": "string" } } } ``` The response will include the updated booking details with the same structure as the request payload, where the values may be modified based on the update operation.
